This project is a monorepo of multiple apps. I use Vercel's TurboRepo to manage the build/test/publish/deploy commands. Not all the project's files are useful or up to date. The few in active development are described below. This entire project is very new, unfinished, and experimental. Please help me to refactor, improve, finish, and optimize it.

Apps are in the ./apps folder. All apps are full-stack using NextJS, having both back-end and front-end files. Log app in ./apps/log logs server and user events to the database and visualizes the data in a dashboard. Trade (day trading) app is in ./apps/trade to execute orders and positions and visualize the user's account in the dashboard.

Shared utility packages are in the ./my folder. Most are for server-side javascript execution in NextJS API routes and server actions. Functions for interacting with the database are in ./my/be/sql. Functions for logging and error handling are in ./my/be/cc (cc stands for cloud console because it intercepts, filters, and saves and console logs to the remote database). For front-end apps, a library of common components and functions is in ./my/fe/src

Directory:

./turbo.json - to manage TurboRepo automations and settings
./apps/log - NextJS dashboard for logging and error reporting
./apps/trade - NextJS dashboard for executing market trades and managing positions

./my/fe - NextJS React components, hooks, and utility functions. Please organize any client-side scripts used more than once into this folder.
./my/be - Back-end utility functions and settings. It is a work in progress. Please refactor all files and folders here as needed.

./my/be/sql - interacting with databases
./my/be/cc - error logging and reporting
./my/be/... - miscellaneous back-end functions and files, but they are not finished and most are not used

Use pnpm:

If you need to run `npm i` or `npm install`, run `pnpm i` instead.

Most important:

This is a mono-repo of multiple projects. When running any terminal command including pnpm, please make sure to be in the correct folder. If editing the "Logs" project then `cd ./apps/log`. If editing the "Trade" project then `cd ./apps/trade`.
